LoRA link:

[https://huggingface.co/Kijai/WanVideo_comfy/tree/main/Stand-In](https://huggingface.co/Kijai/WanVideo_comfy/tree/main/Stand-In)

This LoRA is not the traditional kind and it HAS TO connect to the model loader directly.
The goal is to simply face your subject on white background.

Adjust the blocks to swap based on your VRAM, this is a tradeoff between speed and memory usage.

Further VRAM savings are from torch.compile or alternatively using the chunked rope option in the WanVideoSampler -node

fp_16_fast enables "Full FP16 Accmumulation in FP16 GEMMs" feature available in the very latest pytorch nightly, this is around 20% speed boost. 

Sageattn if you have it installed can be used for almost double inference speed
